# Samsung TV Max — Project Context

## What this is
A Home Assistant custom integration (`samsungtv_max`) for Samsung Tizen Smart TVs.
Migrated from a FIBARO HC3 Quick App (Lua). Legacy (pre-Tizen) TVs are explicitly unsupported.

## Domain
`samsungtv_max`  — used in entity IDs, service names, event names, and config-entry keys.

## Key files
- `custom_components/samsungtv_max/` — the integration
- `custom_components/samsungtv_max/tizen/` — Tizen protocol sub-package
- `tests/` — pytest test suite
- `scripts/` — deploy helpers (rsync/scp to HA)

## Python version
Python 3.12+. Use `from __future__ import annotations` in every module.

## Style
- Line length: 100 (ruff config)
- ruff select: E, F, I, UP, B, SIM
- Type hints everywhere; `from __future__ import annotations` at top
- No bare `except:` — always `except Exception:` with `# noqa: BLE001` if intentional

## Naming conventions
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` in `const.py`
- Config-entry data keys: `CONF_*` constants, never raw strings
- HA event names: `samsungtv_max_*` (underscore, lowercase)
- Service names: `send_key`, `launch_app`, `enumerate_apps`

## No legacy TCP
This integration supports Tizen WebSocket only.
If a device does not respond to GET /api/v2/ with JSON, it is unsupported.
Never add TCPSocket / raw-socket code.

## No SmartThings (yet)
SmartThings API integration is planned but not implemented.
Do not add SmartThings code until explicitly asked.
